The paper deals with the problem of super-resolution and compressed sensing, which are topics typically studied in the Information Theory (cs.IT), Signal Processing (cs.SP), and Numerical Analysis (cs.NA) sub-categories. The proposed method also involves promoting sparsity, which is a common theme in the Sparse and Low-rank Modeling (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper focuses on direction of arrival (DOA) estimation, which is a specific application of signal processing and falls under the Signal and Image Processing (cs.SI) sub-category.
